CAPE Town City have moved swiftly to tie down one of their star players. The Citizens have secured the services of star midfielder Thabo Nodada for a further three years. Nodada has penned a deal that will keep him in Cape Town until 2024. The Citizens' vice captain  has been one of the best players in the league and as a result has attracted interest from other teams. He has made 14 appearances for City this season, scoring four goals and providing one assist. "The club is delighted to have signed a new contract with Thabo Nodada," the Citizens confirmed on social media. "Our vice captain extends his stay until June 2024! An integral figure in the City midfield."